I’m so happy to present my Second model for my upcoming exhibition @smallisbeautifulart ! 

‘The Atelier Window’ - 2022

This is one of my favourites from the new collection of models I have made! I wish to have a studio like this someday! 

The theme of my new collection of models is based on different types of windows and a cozy and dreamy atmosphere inside the room! I love the beautiful and soft light leak from the stained glass windows and it would feel so lovely to work in such a beautiful atmosphere with a cup of hot coffee! 

Please show some love and save and share my work! It would mean a lot to me! 🦋🙏

Music credit - Follow Tama’s Little Music Shop on YouTube and ring the bell 🔔

‘The Atelier window’

Thank you so much for showing a lot of love for this model! 🥰 I’m so pleased! 

This is my favourite model so I keep wanting to post it more ❤️
I used to listen to this song ‘Starlight’ when I was making this model and made me feel nostalgic so it only made sense to use it for this video! 

I truly enjoyed making it and I’m very grateful for all of your lovely words regarding this model! 

Thank you again ❤️

Miniature Pottery and Ceramics 

Scale 1/12 

This is my first batch of miniature ceramics that I’ve tried! I’m so excited because I can now make ceramics. It’s a skill I’ve wanted to learn since many years! I’ll practice more to perfect the different shapes and glazes. 🌚✨

Hello!! 🎠

I’m so excited to let you all know that I now have a YouTube Channel (Pink Petit Rose)! 🥰

The link to my channel is in my Bio. 

I wanted to open a YouTube channel since many years but I never felt confident. Finally, I’ve done it. You can expect art vlogs and tutorials on there!🤗

Please subscribe, like and share! It is free. It will motivate me to keep making new videos for YouTube. 

My first video is about How to make a realistic miniature stone wall. Please watch the full tutorial on my YouTube. The dollhouse kit is by the amazing @giuliasminiatures 🥰

I’ve planned to document my process of working on this dollhouse on YouTube. 

Thank you for subscribing if you have and let me know if you like it! 🥰❤️

.

The last few weeks have been extremely tough for me and my family. We are dealing with some serious medical emergencies and it has been extremely tough for all of us! Right when we thought everything was better and going back to normal we were told a news which has shook us completely. It’s been really hard emotionally and physically dealing with it and I just want you all to please keep my family in your prayers 🙏

It has been hard to get back to work as well as I’m mentally not doing well so I had even decided to take a break and cancel all my collaborations etc. But I think it would be better to work as it would distract my mind and help me feel better. 
So please excuse me if I’m not able to reply back or post as normal. 😞

I really forced myself today to take this video and it did make me feel good 💗

Thank you so much for understanding 🙏❤️

Finally completed my dollhouse kit from @giuliasminiatures!! It is such a easy and nice kit to assemble. I have then added my own style to it. The kit is plain MDF. I made some changes to it by cutting more windows and doors. 

It took me a very long time to complete as I had to take many breaks in between because of some medical emergencies in my family. But all is better now ❤️ and I’m happy I could finally finish it ☺️! 

I have a tutorial on how I made the stone wall on my YouTube channel. This is the first dollhouse I’ve made, so it’s special 💐

Hello everyone! I am currently in the UK for some time and I’m finally sharing this amazingly beautiful 1940’s train cabin kit @byanavrin that was kindly sent to me ❤️
I made it in about 5-6 days, however I was in a rush as I had to urgently travel to the UK. I literally finished making it 5 hours before I was supposed to travel and took these videos! Unfortunately, something went wrong and the moving train mechanism didn’t work! I felt so bad because I was really excited for it, but I didn’t have the time to see what was wrong! But, I asked my father who is in India to look into it and he’s got it working!! 😍 I’m so excited because it looks magical! I didn’t change much in it because I really loved the original design. I’ve only changed the seat colour and made it a bit more vintage looking! 

There were a few other things like little suitcases which I couldn’t make, but my father is making those for me ❤️🥹, just shows that’s it’s a beginner friendly kit! 

Definitely head over to @byanavrin to see the other versions of this train cabin! Its an extremely well designed kit and a joy to put it together! It’s a shame that the background in my video is not moving, but soon I’ll post a video of it when my father sends it to me ❤️

Hello 🦋

As you all know I’m in England for some time! I’m so lucky and happy to have my own little space to work. It’s a nice little cozy place that I decorated in my style. I feel inspired to sit and work there ❤️

Hope I can be more active on instagram now 😄
